Slackware Current Repository by Conraid

======================================================================

pspy (Monitor linux processes without root permissions)

pspy is a command line tool designed to snoop on processes without
the need for root permissions. It allows you to see commands run by
other users, cron jobs, etc. as they execute. Great for enumeration
of Linux systems in CTFs. Also great to demonstrate your colleagues
why passing secrets as arguments on the command line is a bad idea.

HOME: https://github.com/DominicBreuker/pspy

